52
0:02:15.26,000 --> 0:02:18,000
Dr. Faye Miller does something called psychographics,

53
0:02:18.26,000 --> 0:02:21,000
which first came about in the 1960s,

54
0:02:21.26,000 --> 0:02:23,000
where you create these complex psychological profiles

55
0:02:23.26,000 --> 0:02:25,000
of consumers.

56
0:02:25.26,000 --> 0:02:28,000
But psychographics really haven't had a huge impact on the media business.

57
0:02:28.26,000 --> 0:02:31,000
It's really just been basic demographics.

58
0:02:32.26,000 --> 0:02:35,000
So I'm at the Norman Lear Center at USC,

59
0:02:35.26,000 --> 0:02:38,000
